FuncDef:
The set cipher-suite command specifies encryption algorithms to be supported in an SSL cipher suite bound to an SSL policy.
The undo set cipher-suite command deletes encryption algorithms from an SSL cipher suite bound to an SSL policy. The set cipher-suite command specifies encryption algorithms to be supported in an SSL cipher suite bound to an SSL policy. The undo set cipher-suite command deletes encryption algorithms from an SSL cipher suite bound to an SSL policy. By default, no encryption algorithms are supported in the SSL cipher suite bound to an SSL policy.
